# Icebreaker App

## Stack
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, zero build step
- Firebase Realtime Database (compat SDK v10.14.x)
- Chart.js 4.x, wordcloud2.js, all via CDN
- Hosted on GitHub Pages

## Colors (aligned with Beamer presentation)
- `--arca-red: #C82B40` (primary accent)
- `--arca-dark: #6B1525` (dark accent)
- `--arca-crimson: #A31545`
- Background: dark theme (`#0d0709` base)
- Text: white/light on dark

## Structure
- `index.html` — responsive survey (wizard, 8 questions)
- `dashboard.html` — real-time dashboard (8 charts + QR)
- `js/config.js` — Firebase credentials (gitignored)
- `js/survey.js` — question data + wizard logic
- `js/dashboard.js` — charts + Firebase listeners

## Rules
- Keep all dependencies on CDN (no npm/node)
- `DEMO_MODE = true` in config.js enables local testing without Firebase
- Session ID passed via `?s=SESSION_ID` query parameter
- Tone: professional, corporate Spanish ("nosotros")
- Survey questions are strategic/andragogic, not generic
